title: For Sale:  Hi point pistols
postcontent:
Got a pair of good ol' hi point pistols for sale that I've had 4 or 5 years. There is a 40 s&w (tan) and a 9mm (yellow). What can I say about these gems, the 40 is actually an excellent piece once you look past its ugly appearance and those brick like ergonomics. It shoots extremely accurate and functions perfectly, aside from being bulky and nose heavy this one truthfully is a shooter, I don't have very many rounds through the 40 guessing less than 200. On to the 9mm, this one isnt as bulky since its considered a compact by hi points standards, this one isn't near as accurate and doesn't function near as well, it was terrible when I got it but with some polishing I've got most of the kinks worked out but it'll still give you a stove pipe for every box of ammo, this one I've put some ammo through, which is ironic considering its the least accurate and least reliable but I'm guessing there's around 1000 rounds through it. All and all they are cheap fun, both have been powder coated, neither has been sighted in since then, the 9mm has some chips.
I want $200 for the pair and that's firm, I'm including 4 boxes of 40 ammo that's worth $80 right there so basically at $60 each for the guns, and no I wont separate and sell one for 60, its all or nothing, I'm not including any 9mm ammo since I have 2 other 9mm's. Any questions just shoot me an email.
